data.name: Generate car plate numbers
data.description:
Some country have next rules for generating car numbers.
* Use only from alphabet letters collection: *A B C E H K M O P T Y X*
* Number format is [ __LETTER | DIGIT | DIGIT | DIGIT | LETTER | LETTER__ ]

In this Kata we must generate all possible variants for car number mask, where some letter or digit is masked by asterisk (*).

For example, for mask `A*00AA` answer will be: 

```["A000AA", "A100AA", "A200AA", "A300AA", "A400AA", "A500AA", "A600AA", "A700AA", "A800AA", "A900AA"]```

Some advices:
* Uppercase for letters
* Dont forget use `sort` for answer

In this Kata must be only one asterisk mask for digit and letter (maximym only one letter and one digit can be masked) . For example, `A*09*C`.
